                <tr>
                  <td class="tit_icon">Membership &amp; Classes</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="text">&ldquo;member &ldquo; means a person. who is exclusively  practicing vis-a-vis consultancy prominently is the subjects of employees&lsquo;  state insurance; provident fund other industrial law related matters and  includes associate and harmony members.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td height="15"></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="tit_icon">Class Of Members </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="text">There shall be following classes of members of association.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5">
                      <tr>
                        <td width="2%" valign="top"><img src="images/bull.jpg" width="6" height="6" vspace="4" /></td>
                        <td width="98%" align="left" class="text"><strong>Founder Members</strong></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td valign="top">&nbsp;</td>
                        <td align="left" class="text">A person who is exclusively practicing vista  vies consultancy prominently in subject of employees, state insurance,  provident fund, Other Industrial Law and related matters and who is per  register of members enrolled as member on or before 28 Feb. 19995 should be  called Founder Member.</td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td height="15" valign="top"></td>
                        <td height="15" align="left" ></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td valign="top"><img src="images/bull.jpg" width="6" height="6" vspace="4" /></td>
                        <td align="left" class="text"><strong>Honorary Members</strong></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td valign="top">&nbsp;</td>
                        <td align="left" class="text">Any industrial distinguished for public services  or for any nuance or interested in the aim &amp; objects of the association at  a general meeting of the association by a majority of the two thirds of the  members present.</td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td height="15" valign="top"></td>
                        <td height="15" align="left" ></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td valign="top"><img src="images/bull.jpg" width="6" height="6" vspace="4" /></td>
                        <td align="left" class="text"><strong>Ordinary Members</strong></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td valign="top">&nbsp;</td>
                        <td align="left" class="text"><p>A person who is exclusively practicing vis-a-vis consultancy  prominently in subjects of employees state insurance ; provident fund ; other  industrial law and related matter who is as per register of members called as  member after 28 Feb. 19995.should be called ordinary for member . any new  entrant on application for membership and subject to approval of the managing  committee be admitted as ordinary member .</p></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td height="15" valign="top"></td>
                        <td height="15" align="left" ></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td valign="top"><img src="images/bull.jpg" width="6" height="6" vspace="4" /></td>
                        <td align="left" class="text"><strong>Associate Members</strong></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td valign="top">&nbsp;</td>
                        <td align="left" class="text"><p>Any Association or Body of Employers and any employer in  relation to Industrial undertaking or commercial establishment including a  corporate body other than Managing agency and Central Federal Organization of  trade union shall be entitled to be enrolled as an Associate Member of association  upon payment of prescribed fees and upon his or its application for enrollment  being accepted by Managing Committee. Every Associate Member shall be entitled  to appoint a person to act as his or its nominee for every financial year.</p></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td height="15" valign="top"></td>
                        <td height="15" align="left" ></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td valign="top"><img src="images/bull.jpg" width="6" height="6" vspace="4" /></td>
                        <td align="left" class="text"><strong>Life Members</strong></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td valign="top">&nbsp;</td>
                        <td align="left" class="text"><p>A person who is exclusively practicing vis-a-vis  consultancy, prominently in subjects of employees&rsquo; state insurance. Provident  fund, Other industrial law and related matters, may on application to and  subject to the approval by the managing committee of the association, be  admitted as a life member .</p></td>
                      </tr>
                  </table></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td height="15"></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="tit_icon">Rights Of Members</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5">
                      <tr>
                        <td width="2%" valign="top"><img src="images/bull.jpg" width="6" height="6" vspace="4" /></td>
                        <td width="98%" class="text">A founder / ordinary member shall have a right  to attend general meeting of association shall have a right to stand for  selection nomination on managing committee or represent on behalf of the  association etc and shall have a right to vote in case of election subject to  article 11.</td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td valign="top"><img src="images/bull.jpg" width="6" height="6" vspace="4" /></td>
                        <td class="text">An Honorary Member &amp; Associate Member shall have a right  to attend a general meeting of the association but shall be right to elect get  elected or vote at the meeting of the general body .</td>
                      </tr>
                  </table></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td height="15"></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><p class="tit_icon">Membership Fees</p></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5">
                      <tr>
                        <td width="2%"><img src="images/bull.jpg" width="6" height="6" /></td>
                        <td width="98%" class="text"><strong>Admission Fees </strong></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td>&nbsp;</td>
                        <td class="text">Admission fee of Rs. 250/ rupees two hundred fifty only per  member is applicable to all categories of membership except &ldquo;Honorary Member&rdquo;. </td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td height="15"></td>
                        <td height="15" ></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td><img src="images/bull.jpg" width="6" height="6" /></td>
                        <td class="text"><strong>Annual Fees</strong></td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td>&nbsp;</td>
                        <td class="text"><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5">
                            <tr>
                              <td><u>Honorary Member</u> : </td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                              <td>No fees shall be payable by an Honorary Member.</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                              <td height="15"></td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                              <td><u>Founder / Ordinary / Associate Member</u> :</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                              <td>Founder/ Ordinary/ Associate Member shall pay an  annual membership fee of Rs. 500/. (Rupess Five Hundred Only.) .The above  members can also pay the Annual Membership fee for a period of five years at a  time.</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                              <td height="15"></td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                              <td><u>Life Member</u> : </td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                              <td>Life member shall pay a one time membership fee of Rs.  5000/- (Rupees five thousand only ) The annual membership fees shall be due and  become payable on the 1st of April <br />
                                Every years.<br />
                                Annual Membership of a Founder/ Ordinary/ Associate member  shall be renewable from <br />
                                Year without payment of admission fees provided ,however, that  for renewal, the annual<br />
                                Membership fees is paid latest by the 30th April  of the year concerned. The membership shall be renewable subject to the  provisions of Article 11.</td>
                            </tr>
                        </table></td>
                      </tr>
                  </table></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td height="15"></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="tit_icon">&nbsp;Termination  Of Membership</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="text"><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5">
                      <tr>
                        <td width="2%" valign="top"><img src="images/bull.jpg" width="6" height="6" vspace="4" /></td>
                        <td width="98%" class="text">Any  member who desire to resign as a member of the Association shall give a written  notice to the Association and he shall cease to be a member of the Association  upon acceptance of his resignation by the Managing Committee or within two  months of the date of his resignation, whichever is a earlier.</td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td valign="top"><img src="images/bull.jpg" width="6" height="6" vspace="4" /></td>
                        <td class="text"><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5">
                            <tr>
                              <td valign="top"><img src="images/bull_news.jpg" width="3" height="4" vspace="6" /></td>
                              <td>Any  member shall, ipso facto, cease to be a member of the&nbsp; Association if :
                                <ul>
                                    <li>he dies</li>
                                  <li> Declared  insolvent and/or of an insane mind by appropriate authority.</li>
                                  <li> Suspended as per Article 12 of this Constitution. </li>
                                </ul></td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                              <td></td>
                              <td height="15"></td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                              <td valign="top"><img src="images/bull_news.jpg" width="3" height="4" vspace="5" /></td>
                              <td>He fails to pay annual membership fee by 30th  April and he shall not be entitled to vote at any&nbsp; general Meeting of the Association, provided  that managing Committee may on request in writing by an individual to be a  member under this sub-article, continue such individual as a member on payment  of his arrears and on such other conditions as it deems fit.</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                              <td></td>
                              <td height="15"></td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                              <td valign="top"><img src="images/bull_news.jpg" width="3" height="4" vspace="6" /></td>
                              <td>Any member acting in contravention of the  objects of the Association or in any manner detrimental to the interests of the  Association or guilty of misconduct, shall be liable for expulsion by a two-  thirds majority of the members present in person&nbsp; and entitled to vote at any General Body  Meeting convened for the purpose. No such General Meting shall be called unless  such member is given a reasonable opportunity of tendering his explanation or  resignation. Where explanation is offered by the member concerned, the same  shall , as far as possible, be circulated amongst the members.</td>
                            </tr>
                        </table></td>
                      </tr>
                  </table></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td height="15" class="text"></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="tit_icon">Suspension Of A Member</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="text">A Member shall be deemed to be suspended as a  member</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="text"><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5">
                      <tr>
                        <td width="2%" valign="top"><img src="images/bull.jpg" width="6" height="6" vspace="4" /></td>
                        <td width="98%" class="text">Upon his being adjudicated as an insolvent, till  such time as her is discharged as an insolvent.</td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td valign="top"><img src="images/bull.jpg" width="6" height="6" vspace="4" /></td>
                        <td class="text">Upon his being convicted for an offence  involving moral turpitude for a period of two years and from the last day of  his suffering the sentence.</td>
                      </tr>
                      <tr>
                        <td valign="top"><img src="images/bull.jpg" width="6" height="6" vspace="4" /></td>
                        <td class="text">Upon his being debarred as a Practitioner by any  of the authority concerned where he is practicing.</td>
                      </tr>
                  </table></td>
                </tr>
